 {"id":"bd-zfjg5","title":"RCH: Add installation logic to install.sh","description":"Add RCH installation to the main install.sh script, in the Dicklesworthstone Stack phase (Phase 9).

Look at how other stack tools are installed in install.sh (e.g., ntm, dcg, ru, ubs). Follow the same pattern:

1. Check if rch is already installed (command -v rch)
2. If not, use fetch_and_run or the verified installer mechanism
3. Verify installation succeeded (rch --version)
4. Optionally set up the daemon (rchd) as a systemd service
5. Log progress with appropriate step numbering

Key considerations:
- RCH has 3 binaries: rch (hook), rchd (daemon), rch-wkr (worker agent)
- On a target VPS, we only need rch and rchd (rch-wkr is for remote workers)
- The daemon should be enabled but may not need to start immediately (workers need separate setup)
- Hook installation (rch hook install) should be done during services-setup, not during initial install
- Consider adding to acfs services-setup wizard for hook configuration

IMPORTANT: The install.sh is the production one-liner installer (hand-written). The generated scripts in scripts/generated/ are reference implementations. Changes here must be made to install.sh directly.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-12T02:41:00.095592448Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T18:53:23.609575Z","closed_at":"2026-03-12T18:53:23.609575Z","close_reason":"done","closed_by_session":"SandyCitadel","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-zfjg5","depends_on_id":"bd-hmuo6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-12T02:41:24.882379407Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-zfjg5","depends_on_id":"bd-qlapk","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-12T02:42:00.942659364Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-zfjg5","depends_on_id":"bd-ztcoc","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-12T02:41:19.911201297Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
